<BaseLayout title="Symbols" description="Public symbols of Vaelinya.">
  <section class="page-section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Artefacts</p>
    <h1>Symbols</h1>
    <p class="lede">Symbols help readers recognise identity, meaning, and repeated marks across Vaelinya.</p>
    <p>A symbol may be worn, carved, drawn, printed, or noticed in a story. It gives a visible sign a reader can recognise as the world grows deeper.</p>

    <article class="panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">First symbol</p>
      <h2>NAVAN — Remember</h2>
      <p>NAVAN means “Remember.” It is the first public symbol-word because it points toward one of Vaelinya’s clearest ideas: truth, witness, and what should be kept alive.</p>
      <p>As a mark, NAVAN can connect to remembrance, return, witness, and careful attention.</p>
      <p><a class="button" href="/language/lexicon/">Read NAVAN in the lexicon</a></p>
    </article>

    <div class="link-list">
      <a href="/artefacts/maps/">Related maps</a>
      <a href="/artefacts/story-objects/">Story objects</a>
      <a href="/language/lexicon/">Words behind symbols</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
